5:
Bare, empty, nearly a black hole.
This town's huge, but there's nothing 
in it.
12:
Gosh, it's falling apart! Let's see here... 
Uh... I think it's somebody's journal?
15:
I can barely read it... And the back 
half's been torn out…
But what's this?
30:
Then it's also where my home and 
family would be, huh?
37:
The sky's been obscured for a long 
time now. Something... went wrong.
39:
But I'm certain they're out there. 
Countless worlds I haven't seen…
45:
Hey, does the World Flipper work both 
ways? Like if it sucked me in here, 
could it shoot me back out?
49:
Do you want to return to your original 
world?
55:
I mean, yeah. But it's also... I don't 
want to stay stranded in one place, 
you know?
64:
I am the keeper of the World Flipper. 
Yet I can't remember how to use it.
65: For all I know, it may be broken.
69:
No... I don't think so. It brought me 
here, right? It's probably in a bad 
mood or something.
74:
Yeah. Maybe if we hit it real hard... 
That always works on machines, right?
79:
Mm... You're right. Violence never 
solved anything. Well, we'll figure 
something out!
81:
Also, could you stop calling me sir? It 
makes me feel like I should be wearing 
a top hat and monocle or something.
93:
Feels like we're around the same age. 
We should be friends—not butler and 
spoiled rich kid, or whatever you were 
going for.
98:
Yeah. Ooh, or some kind of escape 
team! That sounds cool, right, Stella?
109:
Mph...
Huh? What? Did I fall asleep? My bad.
113:
It's fine. It was my watch.
You woke at a good time though. The 
sun's coming up.
121:
Yes. It's at times like this you 
remember she is only a young girl.
124:
Yeah... But she's fearless. I mean, who 
goes up to monsters and asks for 
directions?
131:
Back when I first met her at Starview, 
she felt almost... lifeless. But now, 
she's like fireworks.
134:
I believe Stella was always brave of 
heart. Do you remember when I was 
being hunted by daemons? She leapt 
before me without hesitation.
137:
Yeah. Doesn't get much more heroic 
than that.
140:
...Which reminds me. You still owe 
me the rest of that story. About your 
champion's trials?
143: You didn't tire of listening about me?
146:
Hello? You're a champion? I bet 
people would pay good money to 
buy your autobiography.
149:
Very well. Where did I leave off?
Ah... My meeting with the dragon.
152:
He had more pride than any king, 
and more power than any knight. 
His name was Vagner, and he was 
ruler over all dragons…
